<div class="d-flex justify-content-around">
    <div>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>
            <b>Q:Who is eligable?</b><br>
            A: Full-Serve printing is available to anyone with a &#x00040 ucalgary.ca email and associated UCID#.<br />

            <b>Q: What type of machine/printing material do we use?</b><br>
            A: At the TFDL makerspace we have a Prusa MK3S 3D-Printer. We use  a thermoplastic polymer made strictly
            from renewable resources called PLA filament. This material is BPA free.<br>

            <b>Q: What is the cost to print?</b><br>
            A: $2.00 set up fee + $ 0.30 per gram.<br>

            <b>Q: Acceptable sizing for job submissions?</b><br>
            A: The maximum dimensions for singular object designs are 200 x 200 x 180 mm. Weight limit is 180g.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h2>Submit A Print Job</h2>
        <p>
            Once you have confirmed that your model is of acceptable sizing and weight, please ensure that your model <br>
            is also watertight, more information available at https://transmagic.com/six-reasons-watertight-models-matter/.<br>
            After the above steps are completed, save your model as a .stl file and submit it below. Please contact us if<br>
            you are experiencing any errors with the online form or have questions not answered here.<br>
        </p>
        <div class="center"><a class="btn btn-primary form" href="/fullserveform" role="button">Online Form</a></div>
    </div>
</div>
<div>
    <h2>Printing Policies</h2>
    <p>
        1. TFDL 3D printers may only be used for academic purposes. Usage for commercial purposes is strictly prohibited.<br>
        2. TFDL reserves the right to refuse any 3D printing request.<br>
        3. TFDL is not responsible for model stability and quality. Please ensure that your model is watertight and<br>
        structurally sound prior to submission.<br>
        4. All models must be picked up within 30 days of completion. All models left for more than 30 days become property<br>
        of the library.
    </p>
</div>

